-- California Investment Adviser Pays $70,000 to Settle U.S. Securities Probe
-- B y   K a r e n   G u l l o
-- 2010-09-29T16:16:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/california-investment-adviser-pays-70-000-to-settle-u-s-securities-probe.html
John Valentine, an investment
adviser at San Ramon, California-base Valentine Capital Asset
Management, agreed to return $400,000 to clients and pay a
$70,000 fine to settle a Securities and Exchange Commission
probe alleging that he failed to disclose conflicts of interest,
the SEC said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Gullo in San Francisco at 
 kgullo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
